I’m sharing this on Amy’s behalf. “My dearest Dad has passed away. I was by his side. I will forever miss our long talks where we agreed on everything. He was my guiding light, mentor, and best buddy. My pain runs so deep, I will cry you an ocean. May you be blessed with eternal life as I will think of you in all that I do and embody your teachings. Your last words to me were “look on the bright side” and “not to worry about things you cannot change” - so I will do these with gratitude and humility. I will take care of your only grandson with the care you showed me and nurture his mind and heart with our heritage and beliefs. You will live on in us and forever be remembered. Bye Pops, you were the coolest, I love you.”
So happy to be back in England. See you all in Whitby and London 🖤

Touring Australia for the first time, WavyLand proudly presents the highly anticipated debut tour for @coldcave23 

Cold Cave has become synonymous with the modern-day resurgence of darkwave. Wesley Eisold’s poetic lyrics and rich baritone combined with Amy Lee’s conceptual artistic vision has propelled Cold Cave to perform at world class museums The Getty and The Guggenheim, and perform alongside legends Depeche Mode, Nine Inch Nails, The Cult and The Jesus and Mary Chain among others. Marked by a pitch black aesthetic, crafting melodic synths-capes with jackhammer beats, songs celebrating the contradictory beauty of the human condition, they are cerebral and savage yet sweet and seductive and stylistic heirs to the noir of The Velvet Underground and Joy Division.
